In middle of July, Vietnam still shone as a Covid-19 outlier. No reported deaths, and months without a locally transmitted case. But now the outbreak is back and named a so called "COVID-19 second wave" to the country in August.

Photo: An almost-empty express intercity bus is on the duty at night in the outskirts of Saigon, Vietnam. / 19th Aug 2020.

It seems many of my recent photos document the absence of people in the city, so I may as well make a series. This is the State of IL building/Thompson Center, taken early afternoon on a Friday on a really nice day.
